author: Scott Manley
description:
The US National Transportation Safety Board issued their final report on the implosion of the Titan Submersible in 2023, it's available here with a lot of supporting documents, some more interesting that others.
https://data.ntsb.gov/Docket/?NTSBNumber=DCA23FM036

This follows on from the Coast Guard report issued in August.
https://www.news.uscg.mil/News-by-Region/Headquarters/Titan-Submersible/

The things I find most interesting are their discussion of data forensics, trying to recover data from cameras and computers that were found in the wreckage.

Follow me on Twitter for more updates:
https://twitter.com/DJSnM

I have a discord server where I regularly turn up:
https://discord.gg/zStmKbM

If you really like what I do you can support me directly through Patreon
https://www.patreon.com/scottmanley
title: NTSB's Report On OceanGate Titan Submersible - New Information, Old Conclusions.
